  "prompt": "What universities does Frontline recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Frontline, the social work charity in the UK, primarily recruits graduates from a wide range of universities across the UK and occasionally internationally. They do not specifically target particular universities but look for candidates with strong academic backgrounds and a passion for social work and child protection.\n\n### **Majors They Look For**  \nFrontline recruits graduates from various disciplines, though they particularly value skills and knowledge in the following areas:  \n- **Social Work** (though a degree in social work is not required)  \n- **Psychology**  \n- **Sociology**  \n- **Education**  \n- **Law**  \n- **Criminology**  \n- **Health and Social Care**  \n- **Other related fields**  \n\nThey focus on transferable skills such as problem-solving, empathy, leadership, and resilience, rather than specific degrees. Frontline provides intensive training through their Leadership Development Programme to prepare graduates for a career in social work.\n\nIf you're interested, you can find more details on their official website: [Frontline](https://thefrontline.org.uk/).",
